      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ConvKey\nsha256(secret,\"conv\") — PRIVATE\nNIP-44 conversation key",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "rect_36",
      "originalText": "ConvKey\nsha256(secret,\"conv\") — PRIVATE\nNIP-44 conversation key",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "rect_38",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 2260,
      "y": 490,
      "width": 930,
      "height": 540,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "#f8f9fa",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "frame_28",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 1075,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1076,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "txt_39"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "txt_39",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2274,
      "y": 504,
      "width": 902,
      "height": 512,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#212529",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "frame_28",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1077,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1078,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "New() generates the 128-bit secret once; Parse(code) re-derives both\nvalues deterministically from it — no coordination needed, both peers\ncompute the SAME Room ID and ConvKey purely from the code they typed.\n\n  Room ID  -> the tag every relay event is filtered/subscribed on.\n              Anyone watching a relay can see this tag exists and that\n              SOME room is active under it — it carries no other info.\n  ConvKey  -> the NIP-44 symmetric key used to encrypt/decrypt every\n              event body. Never transmitted anywhere, ever.\n\nSECURITY NOTE, stated explicitly in the security model: addressing (a\nmessage's \"to\" field) is ROUTING, not privacy. Every room member can\ndecrypt every message with ConvKey, even ones addressed to someone\nelse — a WebRTC signal \"to\" the host is still readable by anyone else\nin the room who happens to be listening.",
      "fontSize": 12.5,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "rect_38",
      "originalText": "New() generates the 128-bit secret once; Parse(code) re-derives both\nvalues deterministically from it — no coordination needed, both peers\ncompute the SAME Room ID and ConvKey purely from the code they typed.\n\n  Room ID  -> the tag every relay event is filtered/subscribed on.\n              Anyone watching a relay can see this tag exists and that\n              SOME room is active under it — it carries no other info.\n  ConvKey  -> the NIP-44 symmetric key used to encrypt/decrypt every\n              event body. Never transmitted anywhere, ever.\n\nSECURITY NOTE, stated explicitly in the security model: addressing (a\nmessage's \"to\" field) is ROUTING, not privacy. Every room member can\ndecrypt every message with ConvKey, even ones addressed to someone\nelse — a WebRTC signal \"to\" the host is still readable by anyone else\nin the room who happens to be listening.",
      "lineHeight": 1.35,
      "baseline": 12.5
    },
    {
