    {
      "id": "txt_51",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3364,
      "y": 404,
      "width": 902,
      "height": 612,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#212529",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "frame_40",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1101,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1102,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "internal/nostrx.Transport <-> internal/protocol.Message\n\n* events are kind 29888 (ephemeral), tagged with the public Room ID\n* payload = NIP-44 encrypted JSON; only ConvKey holders can decrypt it\n* message types: hello . leave . state (PlayState) . chat . ready .\n  file-req . signal (WebRTC SDP) . kick\n* Send() waits for a SECOND relay to ack before returning, not just the\n  first — a single ack used to let a message land on only one relay and\n  silently miss a peer subscribed elsewhere\n* inbound decrypt attempts are rate-limited (fixed window) — caps the\n  CPU an attacker can burn flooding the cleartext room tag with junk\n* replay protection: an event older than 90s, more than 30s in the\n  future, or older than the newest event already accepted from that\n  SAME sender is rejected — closes the window where a captured signed\n  event (a kick, a signal) could be replayed verbatim later\n* relay health is scored (latency + consecutive failures); sends go to\n  the fastest reachable relay first, a failing one is benched with a\n  cooldown (with a safety-net fallback if every relay is down)",
      "fontSize": 12.5,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "rect_50",
      "originalText": "internal/nostrx.Transport <-> internal/protocol.Message\n\n* events are kind 29888 (ephemeral), tagged with the public Room ID\n* payload = NIP-44 encrypted JSON; only ConvKey holders can decrypt it\n* message types: hello . leave . state (PlayState) . chat . ready .\n  file-req . signal (WebRTC SDP) . kick\n* Send() waits for a SECOND relay to ack before returning, not just the\n  first — a single ack used to let a message land on only one relay and\n  silently miss a peer subscribed elsewhere\n* inbound decrypt attempts are rate-limited (fixed window) — caps the\n  CPU an attacker can burn flooding the cleartext room tag with junk\n* replay protection: an event older than 90s, more than 30s in the\n  future, or older than the newest event already accepted from that\n  SAME sender is rejected — closes the window where a captured signed\n  event (a kick, a signal) could be replayed verbatim later\n* relay health is scored (latency + consecutive failures); sends go to\n  the fastest reachable relay first, a failing one is benched with a\n  cooldown (with a safety-net fallback if every relay is down)",
      "lineHeight": 1.35,
      "baseline": 12.5
    },
