    {
      "id": "txt_96",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3364,
      "y": 1384,
      "width": 902,
      "height": 612,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#212529",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "frame_85",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1191,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1192,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "internal/streamserver.Server — a tiny LOCALHOST-ONLY HTTP server\n* exposes each in-progress download at http://127.0.0.1:<port>/0, /1 ...\n* serves byte RANGES like a normal video CDN would — but BLOCKS the\n  read until the requested bytes have actually arrived, instead of\n  404ing or returning short reads\n* mpv is pointed at these URLs and has no idea it isn't a real server\n\nbuffer gate: mpv only pauses on REAL starvation (paused-for-cache),\nnever on speculative read-ahead — demuxer read-ahead is raised to\n120s / 128 MiB so a big jitter buffer and an instant start coexist\n(curing the old \"minutes cached but still frozen\" stall)\n\nreadiness gate: a streaming joiner doesn't announce \"ready\" until a\nreal 4 MB cushion of contiguous bytes sits ahead of the START of the\nfirst file — this is what prevents \"press play\" being immediately\nfollowed by a first-frame stall instead of actual playback",
      "fontSize": 12.5,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "rect_95",
      "originalText": "internal/streamserver.Server — a tiny LOCALHOST-ONLY HTTP server\n* exposes each in-progress download at http://127.0.0.1:<port>/0, /1 ...\n* serves byte RANGES like a normal video CDN would — but BLOCKS the\n  read until the requested bytes have actually arrived, instead of\n  404ing or returning short reads\n* mpv is pointed at these URLs and has no idea it isn't a real server\n\nbuffer gate: mpv only pauses on REAL starvation (paused-for-cache),\nnever on speculative read-ahead — demuxer read-ahead is raised to\n120s / 128 MiB so a big jitter buffer and an instant start coexist\n(curing the old \"minutes cached but still frozen\" stall)\n\nreadiness gate: a streaming joiner doesn't announce \"ready\" until a\nreal 4 MB cushion of contiguous bytes sits ahead of the START of the\nfirst file — this is what prevents \"press play\" being immediately\nfollowed by a first-frame stall instead of actual playback",
      "lineHeight": 1.35,
      "baseline": 12.5
    },
