    {
      "id": "txt_107",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 94,
      "y": 2344,
      "width": 902,
      "height": 632,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#212529",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "frame_97",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1213,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1214,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "internal/syncer.Engine.Run — the EXACT SAME loop runs on host and joiner\n\n* every explicit action (pause/play/seek/speed/audio track/subtitle\n  track+delay/playlist jump) carries a VERSION = wall-clock ms\n* highest version wins, everywhere; ties break on largest pubkey — so\n  a correction only ever flows ONE direction, it can never oscillate\n* clock skew is estimated NTP-style on join (round-trip timestamps\n  echoed both ways) and subtracted from every position projection\n* drift > 0.5s -> hard seek; smaller drift (0.05-0.4s) -> a gentle +-3%\n  playback-speed glide instead (Syncplay-style, never jarring)\n* each observed mpv property (pause/speed/sid/aid/subdelay/playlist\n  pos/paused-for-cache) has an ECHO-SUPPRESSION expectation, so\n  applying a REMOTE command locally doesn't get rebroadcast as if a\n  human just did it — without this, every sync would ping-pong forever\n* readiness gate opens once 7 of these observed properties have each\n  echoed back at least once — proof mpv is actually listening, not\n  just that the request was sent",
      "fontSize": 12.5,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "rect_106",
      "originalText": "internal/syncer.Engine.Run — the EXACT SAME loop runs on host and joiner\n\n* every explicit action (pause/play/seek/speed/audio track/subtitle\n  track+delay/playlist jump) carries a VERSION = wall-clock ms\n* highest version wins, everywhere; ties break on largest pubkey — so\n  a correction only ever flows ONE direction, it can never oscillate\n* clock skew is estimated NTP-style on join (round-trip timestamps\n  echoed both ways) and subtracted from every position projection\n* drift > 0.5s -> hard seek; smaller drift (0.05-0.4s) -> a gentle +-3%\n  playback-speed glide instead (Syncplay-style, never jarring)\n* each observed mpv property (pause/speed/sid/aid/subdelay/playlist\n  pos/paused-for-cache) has an ECHO-SUPPRESSION expectation, so\n  applying a REMOTE command locally doesn't get rebroadcast as if a\n  human just did it — without this, every sync would ping-pong forever\n* readiness gate opens once 7 of these observed properties have each\n  echoed back at least once — proof mpv is actually listening, not\n  just that the request was sent",
      "lineHeight": 1.35,
      "baseline": 12.5
    },
