      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "config      ~/.config/junto/config.toml — hand-rolled flat key=value\n            parser (no TOML library); UNKNOWN keys are a hard error so\n            a typo (e.g. in \"telemetry\") never fails silently\ndebug       -debug -> JSON-line log at ~/.cache/junto/debug-<ts>.log;\n            a nil-safe Logger, so every call site logs unconditionally\ntelemetry   one anonymous ping on create/join: version, outcome, relay\n            latency — no PII, no room secret, no file names; fired\n            synchronously (bounded 3s) so it isn't lost on exit\ndoctor      preflight: mpv . relay reachability . STUN/TURN . disk\n            space . yt-dlp/ffmpeg -> one clear verdict at the end\nselfupdate  `junto update` downloads + SHA-256-verifies against\n            checksums.txt; Homebrew/go-install installs delegate to\n            `brew`/`go install` instead of self-replacing that file\n\nRECAP: relays carry kilobytes of encrypted coordination (modules 3-4);\nWebRTC carries every byte of actual video (modules 5-8); the sync\nengine keeps everyone in lockstep with no leader (modules 9-10);\neverything in this box just supports that, and isn't load-bearing for\nthe watch party itself.",
      "fontSize": 12.5,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "rect_142",
      "originalText": "config      ~/.config/junto/config.toml — hand-rolled flat key=value\n            parser (no TOML library); UNKNOWN keys are a hard error so\n            a typo (e.g. in \"telemetry\") never fails silently\ndebug       -debug -> JSON-line log at ~/.cache/junto/debug-<ts>.log;\n            a nil-safe Logger, so every call site logs unconditionally\ntelemetry   one anonymous ping on create/join: version, outcome, relay\n            latency — no PII, no room secret, no file names; fired\n            synchronously (bounded 3s) so it isn't lost on exit\ndoctor      preflight: mpv . relay reachability . STUN/TURN . disk\n            space . yt-dlp/ffmpeg -> one clear verdict at the end\nselfupdate  `junto update` downloads + SHA-256-verifies against\n            checksums.txt; Homebrew/go-install installs delegate to\n            `brew`/`go install` instead of self-replacing that file\n\nRECAP: relays carry kilobytes of encrypted coordination (modules 3-4);\nWebRTC carries every byte of actual video (modules 5-8); the sync\nengine keeps everyone in lockstep with no leader (modules 9-10);\neverything in this box just supports that, and isn't load-bearing for\nthe watch party itself.",
      "lineHeight": 1.35,
      "baseline": 12.5
    }
